Vietnamese President Confirms Death Penalty for Drug Dealers
HANOI , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- Vietnamese President Tram Duc Luong has confirmed the death penalty for seven members of a drug trafficking syndicate and granted clemency to the eighth , Vietnam News Agency reported Friday .
The eight condemned had asked Tram for clemency after Vietnam 's Supreme People 's Court rejected their appeals against the sentencing by the Hanoi People 's Court last May .
Evidence submitted to the courts showed that the syndicate had smuggled 224 kilograms of heroin into Vietnam from Laos within about three years .
The drug syndicate , which was exposed in June in 1996 , included policemen working for the Interior Ministry , border guards , customs officers and private traders .
